@page "/global-styles";
@using Blazor_Foundation_6_Test_Shared.Components.Containers.Section;
@using OpenCodeDev.Blazor.Foundation.Components.Plugins.StyleManager;
@inject NavigationManager NavManager;
@inject IStyleManagement StyleManager;
<SectionWrapper>
    <SectionLeft>
        <h2>Colors</h2>
        <p style=" margin-top: 1em;margin-bottom: 1em; ">
            Foundation has an accessible default color palette. The primary color is used for interactive elements, such as links and buttons.
            The secondary, success, warning, and alert colors are used to give more context to UI elements and actions.
        </p>
        <TableWrapper class="hover">
            <TableHeader>
                <TableHeaderItem></TableHeaderItem>
                <TableHeaderItem>Value</TableHeaderItem>
                <TableHeaderItem>Property</TableHeaderItem>

            </TableHeader>
            <TableBody>

                @foreach (var style in StyleManager.GetAll())
                {
                    @if (StyleManager.Get(style.Key, "desc") != "hide")
                    {
                        <TableBodyRow>
                            <TableBodyRowItem>
                                <div style=" @($"height: 2.5em;width: 1em; {($"background-color: {StyleManager.Get(style.Key)};")}") ">

                                </div>
                            </TableBodyRowItem>
                            <TableBodyRowItem>@StyleManager.Get(style.Key)</TableBodyRowItem>
                            <TableBodyRowItem>
                                @style.Key.ToString()
                                <p style="padding-left: 1.2em;">
                                    <small>@StyleManager.Get(style.Key, "desc")</small>
                                </p>
                                
                                
                            </TableBodyRowItem>
                        </TableBodyRow>
                    }

                }
            </TableBody>
            </TableWrapper>
            <hr />
        </SectionLeft>
</SectionWrapper>

<SectionWrapper>
    <SectionLeft>
        <h2>Changing the Color Palette</h2>
        <p>There are multiple ways to change the color palette in Blazor Foundation 6.</p>

        <h3>SASS Version</h3>
        <p>ZURB Foundation 6 supports SASS, Blazor Foundation 6 doesn't by default. So, you CANNOT use a compiled version of it because if you do, some components wont receive the updates.</p>

        <p>Note: You can use ZURB Generator to compile yourself a new css but, the color will be overriden by blazor.foundation.css. The rest will stay like font-family.</p>

        <p>Blazor Foundation 6 is built on the basis of Blazor itself... Dynamic updates, that is why we use <NavLink href="/style-management">Style Management System</NavLink> to manage the color palette so it can be change dynamically.</p>

        <h3>Style Management System</h3>
        <p>The best way to change the color palette in BF6 is to use the <NavLink href="/style-management">Style Management System</NavLink>.</p>
        <hr />
    </SectionLeft>
</SectionWrapper>




